== Target and Mode of Action ==
Because of its sequence homology with other β-toxins, BmKAEP is predicted to bind to site 4 (S4) of [[Voltage-gated ion channel|voltage-gated]] Na<sup>+</sup> channels, at domains I, III and IV.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cestèle |first1=S |last2=Catterall |first2=WA |title=Molecular mechanisms of neurotoxin action on voltage-gated sodium channels |journal=Biochimie |volume=82 |issue=9–10 |pages=883–92 |year=2000 |pmid=11086218 |doi=10.1016/S0300-9084(00)01174-3}}</ref> Its interaction with the S4 loop causes the loop to be maintained at the outward activated position. Therefore, activation of the Na<sup>+</sup> channels shifts towards more negative values,<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cestele |first1=S |last2=Qu |first2=Y |last3=Rogers |first3=J |last4=Rochat |first4=H |last5=Scheuer |first5=T |last6=Catterall |first6=W |title=Voltage Sensor–TrappingEnhanced Activation of Sodium Channels by β-Scorpion Toxin Bound to the S3–S4 Loop in Domain II |journal=Neuron |volume=21 |issue=4 |pages=919–31 |year=1998 |pmid=9808476 |doi=10.1016/S0896-6273(00)80606-6}}</ref> enhancing the channel's activation and promoting spontaneous and repetitive firing. Subsequently, the sodium current amplitude decreases, due to the membrane potential depolarization, thus suppressing [[action potential]]s.<ref name="first article"/>

== Toxicity ==
BmK venom induces a transient phase of contraction followed by a slow progressive [[flaccid paralysis]] in insect larvae.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Gurevitz |first1=Michael |last2=Froy |first2=Oren |last3=Zilberberg |first3=Noam |last4=Turkov |first4=Michael |last5=Strugatsky |first5=David |last6=Gershburg |first6=Eduard |last7=Lee |first7=Daewoo |last8=Adams |first8=Michael E. |last9=Tugarinov |first9=Vitali |title=Sodium channel modifiers from scorpion venom: Structure–activity relationship, mode of action and application |journal=Toxicon |volume=36 |issue=11 |pages=1671–82 |year=1998 |pmid=9792184 |doi=10.1016/S0041-0101(98)00160-3}}</ref> However, since it requires a high dosage to be effective, its toxicity is weak, both in insects and mammals.<ref name="eight article">{{cite journal |last1=Zhou |first1=XH |last2=Yang |first2=D |last3=Zhang |first3=JH |last4=Liu |first4=CM |last5=Lei |first5=KJ |title=Purification and N-terminal partial sequence of anti-epilepsy peptide from venom of the scorpion Buthus martensii Karsch |journal=The Biochemical journal |volume=257 |issue=2 |pages=509–17 |year=1989 |pmid=2930463 |pmc=1135608}}</ref>

